 following contact details:</p><ul><li><span>Email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a></span></li><li><span>Phone number: +1 (818) 435-6613</span></li><li><span>Postal address: 15260 Ventura Blvd., Suite 2230, Sherman Oaks, CA 91403 USA</span></li></ul><p> </p><h2><a id="_Purposes_and_legal_1"></a>Purposes and legal basis for the processing</h2><p>Xsolla processes personal data for the following purposes and on the following legal basis:</p><table><thead><tr><th><p><strong>Purpose</strong></p></th><th><p><strong>Legal Basis</strong></p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><p>To license different software (including computer games) for a fee to the users of the website.</p></td><td><p>Performance of a contract to which the data subject is party.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>To provide smooth functioning of the website by storing users’ information (so that they do not have to reenter it during their current or future website sessions) and with the use of third parties’ hosting, maintenance, and security services.</p></td><td><p>Performance of a contract to which the data subject is party.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>To improve design and functions of the website on the basis of analysis of users’ behavior on the website and aggregate website usage metrics (total number of visitors and pages accessed).</p></td><td><p>Legitimate interests pursued by Xsolla.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>To automatically update the software purchased by the users of the website from Xsolla.</p></td><td><p>Performance of a contract to which the data subject is party.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>To provide the users of the website (at their request) with information on the terms of their probable cooperation with Xsolla or the capabilities of services offered by Xsolla.</p></td><td><p>Necessity of the processing in order to take steps at the request of the data subject prior to entering into a contract.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>For conventional direct marketing and other forms of marketing or advertisement.</p></td><td><p>Legitimate interests pursued by Xsolla.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>For enforcement of legal claims including debt collection via out-of-court procedures; prevention of fraud or misuse of services; IT and network security; for marketing research based on analysis of users’ entries, submissions, and status in any promotions or other activities.</p></td><td><p>Legitimate interests pursued by Xsolla.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>To comply with applicable laws (including copyright, defamation, tax, and data protection laws).</p></td><td><p>Compliance with a legal obligation to which Xsolla is subject.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>For third parties’ conventional direct marketing and other forms of marketing or advertisement; for third parties’ marketing research based on usage and demographic patterns for certain computer programs, content, services, advertisements, promotions or other functions of the website.</p></td><td><p>Consent of the data subject to the processing of his or her personal data.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>To provide targeted advertisement and to evaluate for marketing purposes certain personal aspects relating to the data subject, in particular to analyse or predict aspects concerning the data subject\'s personal preferences, interests, behaviour, and location. </p></td><td><p>Consent of the data subject to the processing of his or her personal data.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>For third parties’ targeted advertisement and evaluation for marketing purposes of certain personal aspects relating to the data subject.</p></td><td><p>Consent of the data subject to the processing of his or her personal data.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><h2>Rights of the data subject</h2><p><strong>Right to access.</strong> The data subject can ask Xsolla to confirm whether or not Xsolla processes his or her personal data. If so, the data subject can access these personal data and can ask Xsolla to explain certain details of the processing. To exercise the right to access, the data subject shall contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><p><strong>Right to rectification. </strong>The data subject can ask Xsolla to correct inaccurate personal data concerning him or her. If it complies with the purposes of the processing, the data subject can ask Xsolla to complete incomplete personal data. To exercise the right to rectification, the data subject shall contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><p><strong>Right to erasure (“right to be forgotten”).</strong> In certain cases, the data subject can ask Xsolla to erase personal data concerning him or her. For example, this applies if (1) the personal data are no longer necessary in relation to the purposes for which they were processed; (2) the data subject withdraws consent to the processing and there is no other legal ground for the processing; (3) the personal data have been unlawfully processed. To exercise the right to erasure, the data subject shall contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><p><strong>Right to restriction on processing.</strong> In certain cases, the data subject can ask Xsolla to mark the stored personal data with the aim to limit their processing in the future. This applies if (1) the data subject contests the accuracy of the personal data; (2) the data subject asks to restrict the use of the personal data when their processing is unlawful; (3) the data subject needs personal data to protect his or her rights when Xsolla no longer needs the personal data; (4) the data subject has objected the processing based on the legitimate interests pursued by Xsolla or by a third party. To exercise the right to restriction on processing, the data subject shall contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><p><strong>Right to objection to processing. </strong>The data subject can object, on grounds relating to his or her particular situation, at any time to processing of personal data concerning him or her which is based on the legitimate interests pursued by Xsolla or by a third party. Xsolla shall no longer process the personal data unless Xsolla demonstrates compelling legitimate grounds for the processing which override the interests, rights and freedoms of the data subject or for the establishment, exercise or defence of legal claims.</p><p>Where personal data are processed for direct marketing purposes, the data subject shall have the right to object at any time to processing of personal data concerning him or her for such marketing. Where the data subject objects to processing for direct marketing purposes, the personal data shall no longer be processed for such purposes.</p><p>To exercise the right to objection to processing, the data subject shall contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>. Xsolla can provide the data subject with other options to exercise the right to objection to processing at the time of communication with the data subject (for example, by “unsubscribe” link in a direct marketing email).</p><p><strong>Right to portability.</strong> When the processing is based on consent of the data subject or on a contract with the data subject, the data subject can receive the personal data concerning him or her, which he or she has provided to Xsolla, in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format and can freely transmit those data to another controller. Where technically feasible, the data subject can also ask Xsolla to transmit the personal data directly to another controller. To exercise the right to portability, the data subject shall contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><h2><a id="_Right_to_withdraw"></a><a id="_Right_of_data"></a>Right to withdraw consent at any time</h2><p>Where processing is based on consent, the data subject can withdraw his or her consent at any time. The withdrawal of consent does not affect the lawfulness of processing based on consent before its withdrawal. To exercise the right to withdraw consent, the data subject shall contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><h2>Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</h2><p>When Article 77 of the General Data Protection Regulation (the GDPR)<sup><a href="#footnote-1" id="footnote-ref-1">[1]</a></sup> applies, the data subject can lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority, in particular in the member state of the European Union of his or her habitual residence, place of work or place of the alleged infringement if the data subject considers that the processing of personal data relating to him or her infringes the GDPR.</p><p><strong>The most important aspects of the data processing</strong></p><p>Data subjects shall pay special attention to the following information on the processing of their personal data which has the most impact on them and processing which could surprise them:</p><ul><li><span>Xsolla processes extensive personal data for marketing purposes including targeted advertisement and profiling and discloses personal data to different third parties to let them process personal data for the same purposes. For details please refer to the following sections of this Privacy Policy:<ul><li><span><a href="#_Categories_of_personal">Categories of personal data concerned</a></span></li><li><span><a href="#_Purposes_and_legal_1">Purposes and legal basis for the processing</a></span></li><li><span><a href="#_Recipients_of_the">Recipients of the personal data</a></span></li><li><span><a href="#_Automated_decision-making">Automated decision-making including profiling</a></span></li></ul></span></li><li><span>Xsolla transfers personal data to many countries that provide different level of protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data. For details please refer to the <a href="#_Transfers_to_third">Transfers to third countries</a> section of this Privacy Policy.</span></li><li><span>Xsolla stores personal data for a long time. For details please refer to the <a href="#_Storage_period">Storage period</a> section of this Privacy Policy.</span></li></ul><p>Data subjects shall also pay special attention to the most important consequences of the processing of their personal data by Xsolla for them:</p><ul><li><span>Data subjects may receive advertisements from many companies from different countries based on a deep knowledge of their personal preferences, interests, behavior and other personal aspects.</span></li><li><span>For a long time, data subjects may suffer data breaches which may lead to unauthorised disclosure of their personal data to the public.</span></li></ul><p>These consequences have a high impact on the data subjects’ fundamental rights to privacy and protection of personal data.</p><p><strong>Further details of the data processing</strong></p><p>The full text of this Privacy Policy is available <a href="https://xsolla.com/privacypolicy">here</a>.</p><p>To refer to the sections of this Privacy Policy please click the headings below.</p><p><a href="#_Data_protection_officer">Data protection officer</a></p><p><a href="#_Legitimate_interests_pursued">Legitimate interests pursued by Xsolla and third parties</a></p><p><a href="#_Categories_of_personal">Categories of personal data concerned</a></p><p><a href="#_Recipients_of_the">Recipients of the personal data</a></p><p><a href="#_Transfers_to_third">Transfers to third countries</a></p><p><a href="#_Storage_period">Storage period</a></p><p><a href="#_Requirement_to_provide">Requirement to provide information</a></p><p><a href="#_Source_of_personal">Source of personal data</a></p><p><a href="#_Automated_decision-making">Automated decisio