span></li><li><span>Tunisia</span></li><li><span>Turkey</span></li><li><span>Ukraine</span></li><li><span>United Arab Emirates</span></li><li><span>United States of America</span></li><li><span>Uzbekistan</span></li><li><span>Vietnam</span></li><li><span>Venezuela</span></li></ul></td></tr></table><h2><a id="_Storage_period"></a>Storage period</h2><p>Xsolla stores personal data for as long as required to achieve the purposes of their processing. Due to their nature, these purposes cannot be achieved in some definite or definable time in the future. To provide fair processing of personal data, Xsolla regularly reminds data subjects that Xsolla processes their personal data and that they have legal remedies to stop this processing.</p><p><a id="_Rights_to_access,"></a><a id="_Rights_of_data"></a><a id="_Rights_of_the"></a></p><h2><a id="_Right_to_lodge"></a><a id="_Requirement_to_provide"></a>Requirement to provide information</h2><p>To enter into a contract with Xsolla and to let Xsolla perform a contract with him or her, the data subject shall provide Xsolla with the following personal data:</p><ul><li><span>full name;</span></li><li><span>email address;</span></li><li><span>PayPal account;</span></li><li><span>home or mobile telephone number;</span></li><li><span>bank account and credit card number.</span></li></ul><p>If the data subject does not provide these personal data to Xsolla, Xsolla cannot enter into and perform an agreement with him or her.</p><h2><a id="_Source_of_personal"></a>Source of personal data</h2><p>Xsolla receives personal data not only from data subjects themselves, but also from payment systems, games developers, social networks, Google Analytics (web analytics service offered by Google), and other privately held sources in the field of internet services.</p><h2><a id="_Automated_decision-making"></a><a id="_Automated_decision-making_including"></a>Automated decision-making including profiling</h2><p>Xsolla analyzes personal data of the users of the website to predict their future requests and to provide them with individual proposals.<br /></p><h2><a id="_Children’s_Privacy"></a>Children’s Privacy</h2><p>Xsolla does not process personal data of children under 13 and takes appropriate measures to ensure that they do not use its services. If you find out that a child under 13 has provided Xsolla with his or her personal data, please contact Xsolla at <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><p><a id="_Data_Security"></a></p><h2><a id="_Your_California_Privacy"></a>California Privacy Rights</h2><p>Under Section 1798.83 of California Civil Code, data subjects that are California residents can ask Xsolla to provide information on disclosure of their personal data to third parties for direct marketing purposes of these third parties. To make such a request, California residents can contact Xsolla via the following email <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><h2><a id="_Changes_to_this"></a>Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2><p>Xsolla may change this Privacy Policy from time to time at its sole discretion. If so, Xsolla notifies the users of the websites about these changes by a pop-up line on the website.</p><ol class="footnotes"><li id="footnote-1"><p> Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 27 April 2016 on the protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data, and repealing Directive 95/46/EC. <a href="#footnote-ref-1">↑</a></p></span></li></ol>',"http.0":"Falsche API-Anfrageparameter","http.001-001":"Authentifizierung wurde vom Benutzer abgebrochen","http.002-040":"Benutzer ist gesperrt","http.003-001":"Benutzername oder Passwort ist falsch","http.003-002":"Benutzer nicht gefunden","http.003-003":"Benutzername bereits vorhanden","http.003-004":"Diese E-Mail ist bereits registriert","http.003-005":"Diese E-Mail existiert nicht","http.003-007":"Der Benutzer ist n