at they have legal remedies to stop this processing.</p><p><a id="_Rights_to_access,"></a><a id="_Rights_of_data"></a><a id="_Rights_of_the"></a></p><h2><a id="_Right_to_lodge"></a><a id="_Requirement_to_provide"></a>Requirement to provide information</h2><p>To enter into a contract with Xsolla and to let Xsolla perform a contract with him or her, the data subject shall provide Xsolla with the following personal data:</p><ul><li><span>full name;</span></li><li><span>email address;</span></li><li><span>PayPal account;</span></li><li><span>home or mobile telephone number;</span></li><li><span>bank account and credit card number.</span></li></ul><p>If the data subject does not provide these personal data to Xsolla, Xsolla cannot enter into and perform an agreement with him or her.</p><h2><a id="_Source_of_personal"></a>Source of personal data</h2><p>Xsolla receives personal data not only from data subjects themselves, but also from payment systems, games developers, social networks, Google Analytics (web analytics service offered by Google), and other privately held sources in the field of internet services.</p><h2><a id="_Automated_decision-making"></a><a id="_Automated_decision-making_including"></a>Automated decision-making including profiling</h2><p>Xsolla analyzes personal data of the users of the website to predict their future requests and to provide them with individual proposals.<br /></p><h2><a id="_Children’s_Privacy"></a>Children’s Privacy</h2><p>Xsolla does not process personal data of children under 13 and takes appropriate measures to ensure that they do not use its services. If you find out that a child under 13 has provided Xsolla with his or her personal data, please contact Xsolla at <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><p><a id="_Data_Security"></a></p><h2><a id="_Your_California_Privacy"></a>California Privacy Rights</h2><p>Under Section 1798.83 of California Civil Code, data subjects that are California residents can ask 