ons of the website.</p></td><td><p>Consent of the data subject to the processing of his or her personal data.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>To provide targeted advertisement and to evaluate for marketing purposes certain personal aspects relating to the data subject, in particular to analyse or predict aspects concerning the data subject\'s personal preferences, interests, behaviour, and location. </p></td><td><p>Consent of the data subject to the processing of his or her personal data.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>For third parties’ targeted advertisement and evaluation for marketing purposes of certain personal aspects relating to the data subject.</p></td><td><p>Consent of the data subject to the processing of his or her personal data.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><h2>Rights of the data subject</h2><p><strong>Right to access.</strong> The data subject can ask Xsolla to confirm whether or not Xsolla processes his or her personal data. If so, the data subject can access these personal data and can ask Xsolla to explain certain details of the processing. To exercise the right to access, the data subject shall contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><p><strong>Right to rectification. </strong>The data subject can ask Xsolla to correct inaccurate personal data concerning him or her. If it complies with the purposes of the processing, the data subject can ask Xsolla to complete incomplete personal data. To exercise the right to rectification, the data subject shall contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><p><strong>Right to erasure (“right to be forgotten”).</strong> In certain cases, the data subject can ask Xsolla to erase personal data concerning him or her. For example, this applies if (1) the personal data are no longer necessary in relation to the purposes for which they were processed; (2) the data subject withdraws consent to the processing and there is no other legal ground for the processing; (3) the personal data have been unlawfully processed. To exercise the right to erasure, the data subject shall contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><p><strong>Right to restriction on processing.</strong> In certain cases, the data subject can ask Xsolla to mark the stored personal data with the aim to limit their processing in the future. This applies if (1) the data subject contests the accuracy of the personal data; (2) the data subject asks to restrict the use of the personal data when their processing is unlawful; (3) the data subject needs personal data to protect his or her rights when Xsolla no longer needs the personal data; (4) the data subject has objected the processing based on the legitimate interests pursued by Xsolla or by a third party. To exercise the right to restriction on processing, the data subject shall contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><p><strong>Right to objection to processing. </strong>The data subject can object, on grounds relating to his or her particular situation, at any time to processing of personal data concerning him or her which is based on the legitimate interests pursued by Xsolla or by a third party. Xsolla shall no longer process the personal data unless Xsolla demonstrates compelling legitimate grounds for the processing which override the interests, rights and freedoms of the data subject or for the establishment, exercise or defence of legal claims.</p><p>Where personal data are processed for direct marketing purposes, the data subject shall have the right to object at any time to processing of personal data concerning him or her for such marketing. Where the data subject objects to processing for direct marketing purposes, the personal data shall no longer be processed for such purposes.</p><p>To exercise the right to objection to processing, the data subject shall contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>. Xsolla can provide the data subject with other options to exercise the right to objection to processing at the time of communication with the data subject (for example, by “unsubscribe” link in a direct marketing email).</p><p><strong>Right to portability.</strong> When the processing is based on consent of the data subject or on a contract with the data subject, the data subject can receive the personal data concerning him or her, which he or she has provided to Xsolla, in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format and can freely transmit those data to another controller. Where technically feasible, the data subject can also ask Xsolla to transmit the personal data directly to another controller. To exercise the right to portability, the data subject shall contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><h2><a id="_Right_to_withdraw"></a><a id="_Right_of_data"></a>Right to withdraw consent at any time</h2><p>Where processing is based on consent, the data subject can withdraw his or her consent at any time. The withdrawal of consent does not affect the lawfulness of processing based on consent before its withdrawal. To exercise the right to withdraw consent, the data subject shall contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><h2>Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</h2><p>When Article 77 of the General Data Protection Regulation (the GDPR)<sup><a href="#footnote-1" id="footnote-ref-1">[1]</a></sup> applies, the data subject can lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority, in particular in the member state of the European Union of his or her habitual residence, place of work or place of the alleged infringement if the data subject considers that the processing of personal data relating to him or her infringes the GDPR.</p><p><strong>The most important aspects of the data processing</strong></p><p>Data subjects shall pay special attention to the following information on the processing of their personal data which has the most impact on them and processing which could surprise them:</p><ul><li><span>Xsolla processes extensive personal data for marketing purposes including targeted advertisement and profiling and discloses personal data to different third parties to let them process personal data for the same purposes. For details please refer to the following sections of this Privacy Policy:<ul><li><span><a href="#_Categories_of_personal">Categories of personal data concerned</a></span></li><li><span><a href="#_Purposes_and_legal_1">Purposes and legal basis for the processing</a></span></li><li><span><a href="#_Recipients_of_the">Recipients of the personal data</a></span></li><li><span><a href="#_Automated_decision-making">Automated decision-making including profiling</a></span></li></ul></span></li><li><span>Xsolla transfers personal data to many countries that provide different level of protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data. For details please refer to the <a href="#_Transfers_to_third">Transfers to third countries</a> section of this Privacy Policy.</span></li><li><span>Xsolla stores personal data for a long time. For details please refer to the <a href="#_Storage_period">Storage period</a> section of this Privacy Policy.</span></li></ul><p>Data subjects shall also pay special attention to the most important consequences of the processing of their personal data by Xsolla for them:</p><ul><li><span>Data subjects may receive advertisements from many companies from different countries based on a deep knowledge of their personal preferences, interests, behavior and other personal aspects.</span></li><li><span>For a long time, data subjects may suffer data breaches which may lead to unauthorised disclosure of their personal data to the public.</span></li></ul><p>These consequences have a high impact on the data subjects’ fundamental rights to privacy and protection of personal data.</p><p><strong>Further details of the data processing</strong></p><p>The full text of this Privacy Policy is available <a href="https://xsolla.com/privacypolicy">here</a>.</p><p>To refer to the sections of this Privacy Policy please click the headings below.</p><p><a href="#_Data_protection_officer">Data protection officer</a></p><p><a href="#_Legitimate_interests_pursued">Legitimate interests pursued by Xsolla and third parties</a></p><p><a href="#_Categories_of_personal">Categories of personal data concerned</a></p><p><a href="#_Recipients_of_the">Recipients of the personal data</a></p><p><a href="#_Transfers_to_third">Transfers to third countries</a></p><p><a href="#_Storage_period">Storage period</a></p><p><a href="#_Requirement_to_provide">Requirement to provide information</a></p><p><a href="#_Source_of_personal">Source of personal data</a></p><p><a href="#_Automated_decision-making">Automated decision-making including profiling</a></p><p><a href="#_Children’s_Privacy">Children’s Privacy</a></p><p><a href="#_Data_Security">Data Security</a></p><p><a href="#_Your_California_Privacy">California Privacy Rights</a></p><p><a href="#_Changes_to_this">Changes to this Privacy Policy</a></p><h2 id="_Data_protection_officer">Data protection officer</h2><p>Data subjects may contact the Data Protection Officer of Xsolla with regard to all issues related to processing of their personal data and to the exercise of their rights under data protection law using the following contact details:</p><ul><li><span>Email: gdpr@xsolla.com </span></li><li><span>Postal address: Ioanni Stylianou, 6, 2nd floor, Office 202, 2003 Nicosia, Cyprus</span></li></ul><p> </p><h2 id="_Legitimate_interests_pursued">Legitimate interests pursued by Xsolla and third parties</h2><p>When processing personal data for some purposes, Xsolla pursues the following legitimate interests:</p><ul><li><span>improvement of design and functions of the website;</span></li><li><span>conventional direct marketing and other forms of marketing or advertisement;</span></li><li><span>enforcement of legal claims including debt collection via out-of-court procedures; prevention of fraud or misuse of services; IT and network security; marketing research.</span></li></ul><p>To obtain information on the balancing test (evaluation of interests of Xsolla and data subjects which allows Xsolla to rely on its legitimate interests as a lawful basis for data processing), the data subject can contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><h2><a id="_Categories_of_personal"></a>Categories of personal data concerned</h2><p>Xsolla processes the following categories of personal data:</p><ul><li><span>identity and contact details of the user (full name, date of birth, age, sex, nickname, profile picture, email address, home or mobile telephone number, address, postal code, PayPal account, bank account and credit card number and billing information);</span></li><li><span>the user’s Internet Protocol address (IP address), geolocation, a unique user ID, version of software installed, system type, the content and pages accessed on the website, dates and times of visits of the website, time zone, the user’s accounts in social networks (including profile picture and information on education, job, marital status); tokens for access to the user’s accounts in social networks, accounts in social networks of friends of the user (including nicknames, profile pictures), history of payments with the use of the website, fingerprint of the user’s device and IP (identification of position) at the time of a payment;</span></li><li><span>“cookies information” of the user (session and persistent cookie files).</span></li></ul><h2><a id="_Recipients_of_personal"></a><a id="_Recipients_of_the"></a>Recipients of the personal data</h2><p>Xsolla discloses personal data to the following recipients:</p><ul><li><span>developers and publishers of the software licensed by Xsolla to the users of the website (the developers and publishers may be located anywhere in the world but mainly they are located in the European Union and the United States of America);</span></li><li><span>payment processors retained by Xsolla to process payments of the users of the website (the processors may be located anywhere in the world but mainly they are located in the European Union and the United States of America);</span></li><li><span>providers of hosting, maintenance, and security services retained by Xsolla to run the website (the providers of these services may be located anywhere in the world but mainly they are located in the European Union and the United States of America);</span></li><li><span>advertising and marketing companies that aggregate personal data from different sources to evaluate certain personal aspects relating to the data subject, to perform marketing research and to provide advertising and marketing services to third parties (these companies may be located anywhere in the world but mainly they are located in the European Union and the United States of America);</span></li><li><span>government authorities including tax authorities and police (it may be government authorities of any country but mainly it is government authorities of the European Union and the United States of America).</span></li></ul><h2><a id="_Transfers_to_third"></a>Transfers to third countries</h2><p>Xsolla transfers personal data to the following countries of the European Economic Area (that ensure a high level of protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data):</p><table><tr><td><ul><li><span>Austria</span></li><li><span>Belgium</span></li><li><span>Bulgaria</span></li><li><span>Croatia</span></li><li><span>Cyprus</span></li><li><span>Czech Republic</span></li><li><span>Denmark</span></li><li><span>Estonia</span></li><li><span>Finland</span></li><li><span>France</span></li><li><span>Germany</span></li><li><span>Greece</span></li><li><span>Hungary</span></li><li><span>Ireland</span></li></ul></td><td><ul><li><span>Italy</span></li><li><span>Latvia</span></li><li><span>Lithuania</span></li><li><span>Malta</span></li><li><span>Netherlands</span></li><li><span>Norway</span></li><li><span>Poland</span></li><li><span>Portugal</span></li><li><span>Romania</span></li><li><span>Slovenia</span></li><li><span>Slovak Republic</span></li><li><span>Spain</span></li><li><span>Sweden</span></li><li><span>United Kingdom</span></li></ul></td></tr></table><p>Xsolla also transfers personal data to the following countries that, under decisions of the European Commission, ensure an adequate level of protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data (adequacy decision under Article 45 of the GDPR):</p><table><tr><td><ul><li><span>Argentina</span></li></ul></td><td><p>Decision 2003/490/EC of 30 June 2003, available <a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32003D0490">here</a></p></td></tr><tr><td><ul><li><span>Canada (commercial organisations)</span></li></ul></td><td><p>Decision 2002/2/EC of 20 December 2001, available <a href="http://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/en/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32002D0002">here</a></p></td></tr><tr><td><ul><li><span>Israel</span></li></ul></td><td><p>Decision 2003/490/EC of 30 June 2003, available <a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32011D0061">here</a></p></td></tr><tr><td><ul><li><span>New Zealand</span></li></ul></td><td><p>Decision 2003/490/EC of 30 June 2003, available <a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A32013D0065">here</a></p></td></tr><tr><td><ul><li><span>Switzerland</span></li></ul></td><td><p>Decision 2003/490/EC of 30 June 2003, available <a href="http://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/en/ALL/?uri=CELEX:32000D0518">here</a></p></td></tr></table><p>Xsolla also transfers personal data to the following countries on the basis of standard data protection clauses adopted by the European Commission and available <a href="http://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/en/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32001D0497">here</a> (standard data protection clauses under Article 46.2 of the GDPR):</p><table><tr><td><ul><li><span>Albania</span></li><li><span>Algeria</span></li><li><span>Armenia</span></li><li><span>Australia</span></li><li><span>Belarus</span></li><li><span>Bolivia</span></li><li><span>Bosnia and Herzegovina</span></li><li><span>Brazil</span></li><li><span>Chile</span></li><li><span>China</span></li><li><span>Colombia</span></li><li><span>Costa Rica</span></li><li><span>Dominican Republic</span></li><li><span>Ecuador</span></li><li><span>Egypt</span></li><li><span>Georgia</span></li><li><span>Greenland</span></li><li><span>Guatemala</span></li><li><span>Hong Kong</span></li><li><span>India</span></li></ul></td><td><ul><li><span>Indonesia</span></li><li><span>Iran</span></li><li><span>Iraq</span></li><li><span>Japan</span></li><li><span>Jordan</span></li><li><span>Kazakhstan</span></li><li><span>South Korea</span></li><li><span>Kyrgyzstan</span></li><li><span>Lebanon</span></li><li><span>Malaysia</span></li><li><span>Martinique</span></li><li><span>Mexico</span></li><li><span>Moldova</span></li><li><span>Mongolia</span></li><li><span>Montenegro</span></li><li><span>Morocco</span></li><li><span>Nepal</span></li><li><span>Nicaragua</span></li><li><span>Pakistan</span></li><li><span>Paraguay</span></li></ul></td><td><ul><li><span>Peru</span></li><li><span>Philippines</span></li><li><span>Russia</span></li><li><span>Saudi Arabia</span></li><li><span>Singapore</span></li><li><span>Serbia</span></li><li><span>South Africa</span></li><li><span>Taiwan</span></li><li><span>Thailand</span></li><li><span>Tunisia</span></li><li><span>Turkey</span></li><li><span>Ukraine</span></li><li><span>United Arab Emirates</span></li><li><span>United States of America</span></li><li><span>Uzbekistan</span></li><li><span>Vietnam</span></li><li><span>Venezuela</span></li></ul></td></tr></table><h2><a id="_Storage_period"></a>Storage period</h2><p>Xsolla stores personal data for as long as required to achieve the purposes of their processing. Due to their nature, these purposes cannot be achieved in some definite or definable time in the future. To provide fair processing of personal data, Xsolla regularly reminds data subjects that Xsolla processes their personal data and that they have legal remedies to stop this processing.</p><p><a id="_Rights_to_access,"></a><a id="_Rights_of_data"></a><a id="_Rights_of_the"></a></p><h2><a id="_Right_to_lodge"></a><a id="_Requirement_to_provide"></a>Requirement to provide information</h2><p>To enter into a contract with Xsolla and to let Xsolla perform a contract with him or her, the data subject shall provide Xsolla with the following personal data:</p><ul><li><span>full name;</span></li><li><span>email address;</span></li><li><span>PayPal account;</span></li><li><span>home or mobile telephone number;</span></li><li><span>bank account and credit card number.</span></li></ul><p>If the data subject does not provide these personal data to Xsolla, Xsolla cannot enter into and perform an agreement with him or her.</p><h2><a id="_Source_of_personal"></a>Source of personal data</h2><p>Xsolla receives personal data not only from data subjects themselves, but also from payment systems, games developers, social networks, Google Analytics (web analytics service offered by Google), and other privately held sources in the field of internet services.</p><h2><a id="_Automated_decision-making"></a><a id="_Automated_decision-making_including"></a>Automated decision-making including profiling</h2><p>Xsolla analyzes personal data of the users of the website to predict their future requests and to provide them with individual proposals.<br /></p><h2><a id="_Children’s_Privacy"></a>Children’s Privacy</h2><p>Xsolla does not process personal data of children under 13 and takes appropriate measures to ensure that they do not use its services. If you find out that a child under 13 has provided Xsolla with his or her personal data, please contact Xsolla at <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><p><a id="_Data_Security"></a></p><h2><a id="_Your_California_Privacy"></a>California Privacy Rights</h2><p>Under Section 1798.83 of California Civil Code, data subjects that are California residents can ask Xsolla to provide information on disclosure of their personal data to third parties for direct marketing purposes of these third parties. To make such a request, California residents can contact Xsolla via the following email <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><h2><a id="_Changes_to_this"></a>Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2><p>Xsolla may change this Privacy Policy from time to time at its sole discretion. If so, Xsolla notifies the users of the websites about these changes by a pop-up line on the website.</p><ol class="footnotes"><li id="footnote-1"><p> Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 27 April 2016 on the protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data, and repealing Directive 95/46/EC. <a href="#footnote-ref-1">↑</a></p></span></li></ol>',"http.0":"잘못된 API 요청 매개변수","http.001-001":"사용자가 인증을 취소함","http.002-040":"해당 계정을 사용할 수 없습니다.","http.003-001":"잘못된 사용자 이름 또는 암호","http.003-002":"사용자를 찾을 수 없습니다.","http.003-003":"이미 사용 중인 사용자 이름","http.003-004":"이 이메일은 이미 등록되어 있습니다.","http.003-005":"이메일이 존재하지 않습니다.","http.003-007":"사용자가 활성화되지 않음(확인되지 않은 이메일)","http.003-008":"이메일 변경이 허용되지 않음","http.003-009":"이 이메일을 사용하는 사용자가 이미 존재함","http.003-010":"이메일 전송 중 오류 발생","http.003-011":"확인되지 않은 이메일","http.003-020":"프로젝트에서 이 방식은 사용할 수 없습니다.","http.003-021":"이 프로젝트에서는 사용자 이름/암호를 통한 인증이 비활성화되어 있음","http