ing legitimate interests:</p><ul><li><span>improvement of design and functions of the website;</span></li><li><span>conventional direct marketing and other forms of marketing or advertisement;</span></li><li><span>enforcement of legal claims including debt collection via out-of-court procedures; prevention of fraud or misuse of services; IT and network security; marketing research.</span></li></ul><p>To obtain information on the balancing test (evaluation of interests of Xsolla and data subjects which allows Xsolla to rely on its legitimate interests as a lawful basis for data processing), the data subject can contact Xsolla via the following email: <a href="mailto:support@xsolla.com">support@xsolla.com</a>.</p><h2><a id="_Categories_of_personal"></a>Categories of personal data concerned</h2><p>Xsolla processes the following categories of personal data:</p><ul><li><span>identity and contact details of the user (full name, date of birth, age, sex, nickname, profile picture, email address, home or mobile telephone number, address, postal code, PayPal account, bank account and credit card number and billing information);</span></li><li><span>the user’s Internet Protocol address (IP address), geolocation, a unique user ID, version of software installed, system type, the content and pages accessed on the website, dates and times of visits of the website, time zone, the user’s accounts in social networks (including profile picture and information on education, job, marital status); tokens for access to the user’s accounts in social networks, accounts in social networks of friends of the user (including nicknames, profile pictures), history of payments with the use of the website, fingerprint of the user’s device and IP (identification of position) at the time of a payment;</span></li><li><span>“cookies information” of the user (session and persistent cookie files).</span></li></ul><h2><a id="_Recipients_of_personal"></a><a id="_Recipients_of_the"></a>Recipients of the personal data</h2><p>Xsolla discloses personal data to the following recipients:</p><ul><li><span>developers and publishers of the software licensed by Xsolla to the users of the website (the developers and publishers may be located anywhere in the world but mainly they are located in the European Union and the United States of America);</span></li><li><span>payment processors retained by Xsolla to process payments of the users of the website (the processors may be located anywhere in the world but mainly they are located in the European Union and the United States of America);</span></li><li><span>providers of hosting, maintenance, and security services retained by Xsolla to run the website (the providers of these services may be located anywhere in the world but mainly they are located in the European Union and the United States of America);</span></li><li><span>advertising and marketing companies that aggregate personal data from different sources to evaluate certain personal aspects relating to the data subject, to perform marketing research and to provide advertising and marketing services to third parties (these companies may be located anywhere in the world but mainly they are located in the European Union and the United States of America);</span></li><li><span>government authorities including tax authorities and police (it may be government authorities of any country but mainly it is government authorities of the European Union and the United States of America).</span></li></ul><h2><a id="_Transfers_to_third"></a>Transfers to third countries</h2><p>Xsolla transfers personal data to the following countries of the European Economic Area (that ensure a high level of protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data):</p><table><tr><td><ul><li><span>Austria</span></li><li><span>Belgium</span></li><li><span>Bulgaria</span></li><li><span>Croatia</span></li><li><span>Cyprus</span></li><li><span>Czech Republic</span></li><li><span>Denmark</sp