nal data to the following recipients:</p><ul><li><span>developers and publishers of the software licensed by Xsolla to the users of the website (the developers and publishers may be located anywhere in the world but mainly they are located in the European Union and the United States of America);</span></li><li><span>payment processors retained by Xsolla to process payments of the users of the website (the processors may be located anywhere in the world but mainly they are located in the European Union and the United States of America);</span></li><li><span>providers of hosting, maintenance, and security services retained by Xsolla to run the website (the providers of these services may be located anywhere in the world but mainly they are located in the European Union and the United States of America);</span></li><li><span>advertising and marketing companies that aggregate personal data from different sources to evaluate certain personal aspects relating to the data subject, to perform marketing research and to provide advertising and marketing services to third parties (these companies may be located anywhere in the world but mainly they are located in the European Union and the United States of America);</span></li><li><span>government authorities including tax authorities and police (it may be government authorities of any country but mainly it is government authorities of the European Union and the United States of America).</span></li></ul><h2><a id="_Transfers_to_third"></a>Transfers to third countries</h2><p>Xsolla transfers personal data to the following countries of the European Economic Area (that ensure a high level of protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data):</p><table><tr><td><ul><li><span>Austria</span></li><li><span>Belgium</span></li><li><span>Bulgaria</span></li><li><span>Croatia</span></li><li><span>Cyprus</span></li><li><span>Czech Republic</span></li><li><span>Denmark</span></li><li><span>Estonia</span></li><li